						<summary>

						<p>Stone pillar in the Varadarājasvamin temple, (first side).</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1078,</hi> corresponding to 1156 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record the construction of a temple and consecration of a deity in the temple of Mummaḍi Bhimēśvara by Appana Preggaḍa; <hi rend="italic">Srīkaraṇam</hi> of the temple and the gift of land by him to the deity.</p>						

						</summary>
